			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Best Bard Race<a name="71021"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 14 04 2:10 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I chose half elf because of the starting stats and the night vision.  I belive I put my extra starting points in STR, STA and maybe 5 in CHA.
<br />

<br />
Half elf starting stat comparison:
<br />

<br />
Half Elf vs. Human
<br />
Humans have 5 more STR and STA, but 15 lower AGI and 10 lower DEX.  A 15 point difference on the stats.
<br />

<br />
Half Elf vs. Wood Elf
<br />
Wood elves have 5 more AGI, but 5 lower STR, STA, and DEX.  A 10 point difference in the stats.
<br />

<br />
Half Elf vs. Var Shir
<br />
Var Shirs have 20 more STR and 5 more STA, but 15 less DEX, 10 less INT and CHA.  A 10 point difference in the stats.
<br />

<br />
Overall the Half Elf has very good starting stats for a bard.  I started my bard before Var Shirs existed so I didnt have that option.  I have to admit, the high starting STR is attractive.  However, I'm rarely relied upon for DPS so I dont think I would choose var shir just for the extra STR.
<br />

<br />
In any case, stats aren't the only reason to choose a race but this is how I broke it down 5+ years ago.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
